**Basic Email Layout for Notifications**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Notification Email</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            line-height: 20px;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

       .container {
            width: 600px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

       .header {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
        }

       .content {
            padding: 20px;
        }

       .footer {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            border-radius: 0 0 10px 10px;
        }

       .date-time {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h2>Notification Email</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
            <h3>Notification Details</h3>
            <p class="date-time">Date: <span>{{ date }}</span></p>
            <p class="date-time">Time: <span>{{ time }}</span></p>
            <p>Notification Message: <span>{{ message }}</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>Best regards,</p>
            <p>Your Name</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Variables to Customize:**

*   `date`: The date of the notification
*   `time`: The time of the notification
*   `message`: The notification message

**How to Use:**

1.  Replace `{{ date }}`, `{{ time }}`, and `{{ message }}` with your actual notification data.
2.  Use a templating engine like Handlebars or Mustache to populate the values.
3.  Send this HTML email template as a notification to your users.

This basic email layout provides a clear structure for delivering notifications, with separate sections for the header, content, and footer. The date and time fields are clearly marked for customization, making it easy to populate the values with your actual notification data.

